comments.message:
The names which are defined in the device tree for GPIO LEDs will be given in the entity-manager configuration. Once the interface (xyz.openbmc_project.Configuration.Led) for LED is added in entity-manager dbus path, the dbus signal will triggered in phosphor-led-sysfs daemon and the properties mentioned in that interface will be read. Those properties result will represents the LED name and it will be compared with the /sys/class/leds/ path to check the LED is created or not. IF the LED name does not match with /sys/ path created, then dbus path will not be created.

Example:
DeviceTree:
        leds {
                compatible = "gpio-leds";
                ledName {
                        label = "group:blue:powerled";
                        gpios = <&gpio ASPEED_GPIO(M, 0) GPIO_ACTIVE_HIGH>;
                };
        };

Entity Manager conf:

        {
            "Class": "group",
            "Name": "powerled",
            "Name1": "blue",
            "Type": "Led"
        }

sys path :  /sys/class/leds/group:blue:powerled

This is the approach implemented in phosphor-led-sysfs repository. Only when the interface(xyz.openbmc_project.Configuration.Led) is added in entity-manager, the LED dbus path will be created.
